After moving to Los Angeles, he joined Lester Young's group in 1942.
He recorded Sarah Vaughan with the Jimmy Rowles Quintet with Sarah Vaughan and accompanied Carmen McRae on her 1972 live album The Great American Songbook.
In the 1950s and 1960s, he frequently played behind Billie Holiday and Peggy Lee.
